      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:3:12:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِذَا عَمِيَ الْمَمْلُوكُ فَلَا رِقَّ عَلَيْهِ وَ الْعَبْدُ إِذَا جُذِمَ فَلَا رِقَّ عَلَيْهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘When the owned slave is blinded, so there is no slavery upon him; and the slave, when he is suffers from leprosy, so there is no slavery upon him’."
        ]
      }
    }
